---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Disclaimer";
const description = "Material estimation and engineering disclaimers for HomeProjectHub.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6 py-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-[var(--fg-muted)] mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-[var(--fg)] transition-colors">Home</a>
      <svg class="w-3 h-3" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
      <span class="text-[var(--fg-secondary)] font-medium">Disclaimer</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="pb-6 mb-2 border-b border-[var(--border)]">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-balance mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Disclaimer
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-[var(--fg-muted)] font-mono">
        Last Updated: June 30, 2026
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-pretty">
      <p>
        The calculations, formulas, conversions, and guides provided on HomeProjectHub (accessible at https://homeprojecthub.com) are intended solely for educational, informational, and general planning purposes. 
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Accuracy of Estimates
      </h2>
      <p>
        While we strive to ensure that all algorithms and packaging ratios are mathematically correct and conform to standard building parameters, all outputs generated by our calculators are **estimates only**.
      </p>
      <p>
        Actual material requirements on construction sites frequently differ from theoretical math due to:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)]">
        <li>Soil settlement and compaction rates.</li>
        <li>Bowing or flexing of timber formwork.</li>
        <li>Spillage, waste, and cutting factors.</li>
        <li>Irregular excavation depths and uneven ground grades.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Professional Advice
      </h2>
      <p>
        The information on this website is not a substitute for professional architectural, engineering, or contracting advice. You should not rely on any material counts generated here for ordering high-volume concrete ready-mix deliveries or structural building supplies without first verifying the dimensions with a qualified building professional or contractor.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
